[b]Adaptive Fair Value Cloud[/b] plots a volatility-adaptive channel around a configurable centerline, keeping band width proportionate to current market conditions instead of a fixed multiplier.

[b]What it does[/b]

The cloud is built from a selectable centerline (EMA, KAMA, Regression, or VWMA) and a band width that blends ATR with mean absolute deviation. A regime-adaptive multiplier then widens the bands in expansion, narrows them in compression, and adjusts for trend or range conditions.

[b]Regimes[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Compression[/b] — low volatility percentile, high choppiness
[*][b]Expansion[/b] — high volatility percentile, high efficiency
[*][b]Range[/b] — high choppiness, low ADX
[*][b]Trend Up / Trend Down[/b] — aligned slope, ADX, efficiency ratio, and R²
[/list]

[b]Signals[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Cloud Break[/b] — close crosses the outer band while trending or expanding
[*][b]Fair Value Reclaim/Reject[/b] — close crosses the centerline while trending, without breaching the opposite outer band
[/list]

Both are coincident confirmations — they fire once the move has already happened.

[b]Watch Layer (leading, unconfirmed)[/b]

Three early-warning signals that fire before the confirmed signals above. None of them predict direction with certainty — they flag a rising probability of a move, not a guaranteed one:

[list]
[*][b]Regime Building[/b] — Efficiency Ratio and R² accelerate before the trend gate trips, ahead of a Trend Up/Down flip
[*][b]Squeeze Releasing[/b] — band width was near a multi-bar low and is now widening; a volatility expansion may be starting
[*][b]Divergence at Edge[/b] — price sets a new extreme at the outer band that RSI does not confirm
[/list]

